description: Differences between two positive cubes in exactly 3 ways.
mathematica: r = 5818176; p = 3; Sort@Drop[Flatten@Select[Tally@Reap[Do[n = i^p - j^p; If[n <= r, Sow[n]], {i, Ceiling[(r/p)^(1/(p - 1))]}, {j, i}]][[2, 1]], #[[2]] == 3 &], {2, -1, 2}] (* _Arkadiusz Wesolowski_, Dec 10 2015 *)
crossrefs: Cf. A000578, A181123, A014439 (exactly one way), A034179 (more than one way), A014440 (exactly two ways), A265625 (more than two ways).
author: Glen Burch (gburch(AT)erols.com)
